definitions.definition: Surrounded by land (having no borders with the sea).
examples: Switzerland is landlocked and obviously will never be a great sea power and must always trade overland.
definitions.label_groups: of a country, geographical region, etc.

definitions.definition: Living in freshwater , such as landlocked salmon .
Surrounded by other property and having no access to a public road.
definitions.label_groups: US , real estate , of a property or parcel
